description:
No time to cook? This beer battered Kang kong is SUPER SIMPLE and SUPER EASY. You could cook this for a group of friends for entertaining or for yourself when you don't have to cook.

Although this is a fried dish, beer battered Kang kong is relatively healthier than grabbing a bag of potato chip or any other kind of junk food. After all, this recipe has Kang kong, or water spinach. Kang kong provides a nice crunch in every bite. If you couldn't find Kang kong in your market, you may use your favorite leafy green but I do highly recommend Kang kong first. You'll see the difference. Kain na, let's eat!!

INGREDIENTS LIST:

1 cup all purpose flour 
1 cup light beer 
1-2 pinches of salt
1-2 pinches of black pepper
